Copyright (c) 2015-2026 Michael Iacono, David M. Levinson, Ahmed
El-Geneidy, and Rania Wasfi

This repository is a mixed research package. The license below applies only
to materials that the paper authors or repository maintainers have rights to
license, and it does not relicense excluded, source-map, public-deposit,
public-agency, publisher, shared-source, or third-party materials.

## Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International

Author-created repository documentation, package metadata, source-decision
notes, dependency records, source profiles, and rights-cleared derived package
metadata are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
License (CC BY 4.0):

https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

This includes author-created documentation and metadata describing the local
Rania-Iacono grid supplement under
`data/rania_iacono_grid_land_use_1960_2000/`, and the grid table and geometry
supplement only to the extent controlled by the paper authors or repository
maintainers.

## Materials Not Relicensed

This repository license does not apply to:

- The publication PDFs under `paper/`, which retain their publication,
  repository, or manuscript terms, including the TeMA article terms.
- Historical Twin Cities land-use maps, source-map files, GIS source layers,
  public DRUM/UDC deposits, Metropolitan Council parcel or land-use source
  data, Borchert Map Library source materials, or other public-agency/source
  records.
- The shared historical Markov/Twin Cities land-use source package under
  `_shared_sources/twin-cities-historical-landuse-markov`, which retains its
  own source provenance and public-deposit boundary.
- Local source trees and Dropbox mirrors that are documented as source context
  but are not duplicated or relicensed in this paper-specific package.
- Vendor file-format structures, application metadata, drafts, submission
  materials, final analysis scripts if later found outside this repository,
  cited references, and other third-party or externally controlled materials.

## Software Boundary

No executable software, scripts, notebooks, model source code, regression
scripts, forecast scripts, or paper-specific runtime code are staged in this
repository. This root license therefore grants no separate software license.
